==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} '''[[linea]]''', ''line'', + adjectival suffix '''[[-aris]]'''

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈlɪ.ni.ɚ/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
{{wikipedia}}

# Having the form of a [[line]]; [[straight]].
# Pertaining or related to lines.
# Made in a [[step-by-step]], [[logical]] manner.
# {{botany|of leaves}} Long and narrow, with nearly [[parallel]] sides.
# {{mathematics}} Of, or related to a class of [[polynomial]] of the form <math> y = a.x + b </math>.
# {{physics}} A type of [[length]] measurement involving only one spatial [[dimension]] {{ib|as opposed to area or volume}}.

